---
import Page from '@/layouts/themes/en/Page.astro'
import Svg17 from '@/assets/en/svg/en-svg-17.svg'
import Svg18 from '@/assets/en/svg/en-svg-18.svg'
import Svg36 from '@/assets/en/svg/en-svg-36.svg'
import Svg37 from '@/assets/en/svg/en-svg-37.svg'
import Svg38 from '@/assets/en/svg/en-svg-38.svg'
import { products, site } from '@/config/index.ts'
import { usd, formatNumber, route, getPathLocale } from '@/utils/index.ts'

const locale = getPathLocale(Astro.url.pathname)
const title = "What Is Zuo Yue Zi? The Chinese Postpartum Tradition — JingMommy"
const description =
  "Zuo Yue Zi is the 2,000-year-old Chinese practice of structured postpartum recovery through warmth, rest, and staged nourishment. Learn the three-stage framework, four principles, and what to eat."


const jsonLd = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    headline: "What Is Zuo Yue Zi? The Chinese Postpartum Tradition",
    author: {
      "@type": "Person",
      name: "Nicole Huang",
      jobTitle: "Founder, JingMommy",
    },
    publisher: { "@type": "Organization", name: "JingMommy" },
    about: "Zuo Yue Zi — Chinese postpartum confinement and recovery",
  },
]
---

<Page title={title} description={description} jsonLd={jsonLd}>

  <style is:global>

*{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}
html{scroll-behavior:smooth}
body{
  font-family:'EB Garamond','Georgia',serif;
  background:var(--paper);color:var(--ink);
  line-height:1.7;font-size:18px;
  -webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-moz-osx-font-smoothing:grayscale;
}
a{color:inherit}

.wrap{max-width:1120px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 32px}
.narrow{max-width:760px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 32px}

.eyebrow{font-family:'Jost',sans-serif;font-size:12px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:.32em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--accent-deep);margin-bottom:20px}

h1{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-weight:500;font-size:62px;line-height:1.08;letter-spacing:.005em;color:var(--ink)}
h2{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-weight:500;font-size:46px;line-height:1.12;color:var(--ink)}
h3{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-weight:500;font-size:28px;line-height:1.22;color:var(--ink)}
p{margin-bottom:18px}p:last-child{margin-bottom:0}











.botan{position:absolute;pointer-events:none;z-index:1}
section{position:relative}

.btn{font-family:'Jost',sans-serif;font-size:13px;letter-spacing:.14em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:16px 32px;border-radius:2px;cursor:pointer;text-decoration:none;display:inline-block;transition:all .25s;border:1px solid transparent;font-weight:400}
.btn-primary{background:var(--accent-deep);color:var(--paper)}
.btn-primary:hover{background:var(--ink)}
.btn-ghost{background:transparent;border-color:var(--accent-deep);color:var(--accent-deep)}
.btn-ghost:hover{background:var(--accent-deep);color:var(--paper)}
.btn-sm{padding:13px 26px;font-size:12px}

.hero{position:relative;overflow:hidden;padding:96px 0 112px;background:linear-gradient(180deg,var(--paper) 0%,var(--cream) 100%)}
.hero-inner{position:relative;z-index:3;max-width:880px;margin:0 auto;text-align:center;padding:0 32px}
.hero h1{margin-bottom:30px}
.hero h1 em{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-style:italic;color:var(--accent-deep);font-weight:500}
.hero .lede{font-size:21px;color:var(--ink-soft);max-width:680px;margin:0 auto 28px}
.hero .definition{font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-style:italic;font-size:18px;color:var(--muted);max-width:620px;margin:0 auto 36px;line-height:1.6}
.hero-gift{display:inline-block;font-family:'Jost',sans-serif;font-size:12px;letter-spacing:.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--accent-deep);text-decoration:none;border-bottom:1px solid var(--accent);padding-bottom:3px;transition:all .2s}
.hero-gift:hover{color:var(--ink);border-color:var(--ink)}
.hero-botan-tl{top:-20px;left:-30px;width:300px;opacity:.92}
.hero-botan-br{bottom:-40px;right:-30px;width:330px;opacity:.92}

.band{padding:104px 0;position:relative}
.band-cream{background:var(--cream)}
.band-paper{background:var(--paper)}
.band-deep{background:var(--cream-deep)}

.section-head{text-align:center;max-width:720px;margin:0 auto 64px}
.section-head .eyebrow{margin-bottom:18px}
.section-head p{font-size:19px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:18px}

.outcomes{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:32px;max-width:1000px;margin:0 auto}
.outcome{text-align:center;padding:0 16px}
.outcome-mark{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:48px;line-height:1;color:var(--accent);margin-bottom:18px;font-style:italic}
.outcome h3{font-size:24px;margin-bottom:12px}
.outcome p{font-size:16px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.6}

.feature-quote{max-width:780px;margin:80px auto 0;text-align:center;padding:0 32px}
.feature-quote .q{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-weight:500;font-size:30px;line-height:1.36;color:var(--ink);margin-bottom:26px;letter-spacing:.005em}
.feature-quote .by{font-family:'Jost',sans-serif;font-size:13px;letter-spacing:.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--accent-deep);margin-bottom:6px}
.feature-quote .ctx{font-size:15.5px;color:var(--muted);font-style:italic}

.window-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:.95fr 1.05fr;gap:84px;align-items:center;max-width:1060px;margin:0 auto}
.window-body .eyebrow{margin-bottom:18px}
.window-body h2{margin-bottom:24px}
.window-body p{font-size:18px;color:var(--ink-soft);line-height:1.7}
.window-quote{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-style:italic;font-size:24px;line-height:1.42;color:var(--accent-deep);border-left:2px solid var(--accent);padding-left:24px;margin:30px 0 0}
.window-img{position:relative;min-height:480px;border-radius:3px;overflow:hidden;background:var(--cream-deep)}
.window-img svg{width:100%;height:100%;display:block}

.three-pillars{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:0;max-width:1040px;margin:0 auto;border-top:1px solid var(--line)}
.pillar{padding:48px 36px;border-right:1px solid var(--line);text-align:center}
.pillar:last-child{border-right:none}
.pillar-mark{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-style:italic;font-size:22px;color:var(--accent);margin-bottom:12px}
.pillar h3{font-size:25px;margin-bottom:14px}
.pillar p{font-size:16px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.6}

.principles{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:0;max-width:1040px;margin:0 auto;border:1px solid var(--line);background:var(--paper)}
.principle{padding:48px 44px;border-right:1px solid var(--line);border-bottom:1px solid var(--line)}
.principle:nth-child(even){border-right:none}
.principle:nth-child(3),.principle:nth-child(4){border-bottom:none}
.principle-tag{font-family:'Jost',sans-serif;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--accent-deep);margin-bottom:10px}
.principle-tcm{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-style:italic;font-size:18px;color:var(--accent);margin-bottom:14px;line-height:1.4}
.principle h3{font-size:25px;margin-bottom:14px}
.principle p{font-size:16px;color:var(--ink-soft);line-height:1.65}

.stages-intro{max-width:760px;margin:0 auto 56px}
.stages-intro p{font-size:18px;color:var(--ink-soft);line-height:1.7}

.stages{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:32px;max-width:980px;margin:0 auto}
.stage-card{display:grid;grid-template-columns:200px 1fr;gap:48px;align-items:start;padding:48px 44px;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:3px;background:var(--paper);position:relative}
.stage-card.featured{background:var(--ink);color:var(--paper);border-color:var(--ink)}
.stage-card.featured h3,.stage-card.featured .stage-body p{color:var(--paper)}
.stage-card.featured .stage-week{color:#E8D5C2}
.stage-card.featured .stage-phase{color:var(--accent)}
.stage-card.featured .stage-zh{color:var(--accent)}
.stage-card.featured .reasoning{border-top-color:rgba(255,255,255,.15)}
.stage-card.featured .reason-label{color:var(--accent)}
.stage-card.featured .reason-text{color:#D6CAB8}
.stage-card.featured .p7-link{color:#E8D5C2;border-color:rgba(232,213,194,.4)}
.stage-card.featured .p7-link:hover{color:var(--paper);border-color:var(--paper)}
.stage-card.featured .stage-body p{color:#D6CAB8}
.stage-card.featured .stage-purpose{color:var(--accent);border-color:var(--accent)}

.stage-side{text-align:left;padding-top:6px}
.stage-week{font-family:'Jost',sans-serif;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--accent-deep);margin-bottom:8px}
.stage-phase{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-style:italic;font-size:42px;color:var(--accent);line-height:1}

.stage-body h3{font-size:30px;margin-bottom:6px;font-weight:500}
.stage-zh{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-style:italic;font-size:17px;color:var(--accent-deep);margin-bottom:18px;letter-spacing:.02em}
.stage-purpose{display:inline-block;font-family:'Jost',sans-serif;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--accent-deep);padding:5px 14px;border:1px solid var(--accent);border-radius:2px;margin-bottom:18px}
.stage-body p{font-size:17px;line-height:1.7;color:var(--ink-soft);margin-bottom:0}

.reasoning{margin-top:24px;padding-top:22px;border-top:1px solid var(--line)}
.reason-label{font-family:'Jost',sans-serif;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--accent-deep);margin-bottom:8px}
.reason-text{font-size:15.5px;line-height:1.65;color:var(--muted);font-style:italic;margin-bottom:16px}

.p7-link{display:inline-block;font-family:'Jost',sans-serif;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--accent-deep);text-decoration:none;border-bottom:1px solid var(--accent);padding-bottom:3px;transition:all .2s}
.p7-link:hover{color:var(--ink);border-color:var(--ink)}

.nicole-bar{max-width:880px;margin:80px auto 0;display:grid;grid-template-columns:60px 1fr;gap:24px;align-items:center;padding:32px 36px;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:3px;background:var(--paper)}
.nicole-avatar{width:60px;height:60px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--accent-deep);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:26px;color:var(--paper);font-weight:600}
.nicole-text{font-size:15px;color:var(--ink-soft);line-height:1.65}
.nicole-text strong{font-weight:500;color:var(--ink)}

.midcta{max-width:880px;margin:64px auto 0;text-align:center;padding:48px 48px;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:3px;background:var(--cream)}
.midcta .q{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-style:italic;font-size:24px;line-height:1.42;color:var(--ink);margin-bottom:20px}
.midcta .by{font-family:'Jost',sans-serif;font-size:12px;letter-spacing:.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--accent-deep);margin-bottom:32px}
.midcta-divider{width:48px;height:1px;background:var(--accent);margin:0 auto 28px}
.midcta-price{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-style:italic;font-size:20px;color:var(--ink-soft);margin-bottom:28px;line-height:1.5}
.midcta-buttons{display:flex;gap:14px;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap}

.myths{max-width:840px;margin:0 auto}
.myth-item{padding:36px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line)}
.myth-item:last-child{border-bottom:none}
.myth-item.featured{padding:44px 0}
.myth-q{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-style:italic;font-size:24px;line-height:1.4;color:var(--accent-deep);margin-bottom:20px;position:relative;padding-left:30px}
.myth-q::before{content:'\2715';position:absolute;left:0;top:8px;font-family:'Jost',sans-serif;font-style:normal;font-size:14px;color:var(--rose-deep)}
.myth-a{font-size:17px;color:var(--ink-soft);line-height:1.72}
.myth-a p{margin-bottom:14px}

.myth-sublist{margin:24px 0 14px;padding:0;list-style:none}
.myth-sublist li{padding:14px 0;border-top:1px solid var(--line-soft);font-size:16px;color:var(--ink-soft);line-height:1.66}
.myth-sublist li:first-child{border-top:none}
.myth-sublist .lbl{font-family:'Jost',sans-serif;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--accent-deep);display:block;margin-bottom:6px}

.myth-close{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-style:italic;font-size:19px;color:var(--accent-deep);margin-top:18px;display:block}

.partner{max-width:760px;margin:0 auto;background:var(--paper);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:3px;padding:52px 56px;text-align:center;position:relative}
.partner .eyebrow{margin-bottom:14px}
.partner h3{font-size:30px;margin-bottom:22px}
.partner p{font-size:17px;color:var(--ink-soft);line-height:1.72;margin-bottom:16px}
.partner p:last-child{margin-bottom:0}

.faq{max-width:840px;margin:0 auto}
.faq-item{padding:32px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line)}
.faq-item:last-child{border-bottom:none}
.faq-q{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-weight:500;font-size:24px;line-height:1.32;color:var(--ink);margin-bottom:16px}
.faq-a{font-size:17px;color:var(--ink-soft);line-height:1.72}

.final-cta{position:relative;overflow:hidden;padding:120px 0;background:var(--accent-deep);color:var(--paper);text-align:center}
.final-cta-inner{position:relative;z-index:3;max-width:720px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 32px}
.final-cta .eyebrow{color:#E8D5C2;margin-bottom:18px}
.final-cta h2{color:var(--paper);margin-bottom:22px}
.final-cta p{font-size:19px;color:#F0E4D8;margin-bottom:40px;line-height:1.7}
.final-cta .btn-primary{background:var(--paper);color:var(--accent-deep)}
.final-cta .btn-primary:hover{background:var(--cream);color:var(--ink)}
.final-cta .btn-ghost{border-color:#E8D5C2;color:#F0E4D8}
.final-cta .btn-ghost:hover{background:rgba(255,255,255,.12);color:#fff}
.final-buttons{display:flex;gap:16px;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap}












.reveal{opacity:0;transform:translateY(24px);transition:opacity .9s ease,transform .9s ease}
.reveal.in{opacity:1;transform:none}
section[id]{scroll-margin-top:78px}

@media(max-width:900px){
  h1{font-size:46px} h2{font-size:36px}
  .nav{display:none}
  .nav.open{display:flex;position:absolute;top:100%;left:0;right:0;flex-direction:column;background:var(--paper);padding:24px 32px;gap:20px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line);align-items:flex-start}
  .menu-btn{display:block}
  .band{padding:72px 0}
  .hero{padding:64px 0 80px}
  .hero-botan-tl{width:180px} .hero-botan-br{width:200px}
  .window-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:48px}
  .window-img{min-height:340px}
  .three-pillars,.principles{grid-template-columns:1fr}
  .pillar{border-right:none;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line)}
  .pillar:last-child{border-bottom:none}
  .principle{border-right:none;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line)}
  .principle:nth-child(odd){border-right:none}
  .principle:last-child{border-bottom:none}
  .outcomes{grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:48px}
  .stage-card{grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:24px;padding:36px 32px}
  .stage-side{text-align:left}
  .stage-phase{font-size:32px}
  .nicole-bar{padding:28px 24px;grid-template-columns:48px 1fr;gap:18px}
  .nicole-avatar{width:48px;height:48px;font-size:21px}
  .midcta{padding:36px 28px}
  .midcta .q{font-size:20px}
  .partner{padding:36px 28px}
  .partner h3{font-size:24px}
  .feature-quote .q{font-size:22px}
  .footer-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}
}
@media(max-width:560px){
  h1{font-size:38px}
  .hero .lede{font-size:18px}
  .footer-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}
  .wrap,.narrow{padding:0 22px}
  .stage-card{padding:28px 22px}
  .myth-q{font-size:21px;padding-left:26px}
  .faq-q{font-size:21px}
}
@media(prefers-reduced-motion:reduce){
  .reveal{opacity:1;transform:none;transition:none}
  html{scroll-behavior:auto}
}
  </style>

<!-- TOP BAR -->

<!-- HERO -->
<section class="hero">
  <Svg17 class="botan hero-botan-tl" aria-hidden="true" />
  <Svg18 class="botan hero-botan-br" aria-hidden="true" />

  <div class="hero-inner">
    <p class="eyebrow reveal">Why Zuo Yue Zi</p>
    <h1 class="reveal">If you grew up hearing about <em>Zuo Yue Zi,</em><br>or have no idea how to start —<br>this page is for you.</h1>
    <p class="definition reveal">Zuo Yue Zi (坐月子) — literally "sitting the month" — is the Chinese practice of structured postpartum recovery through warmth, rest, and staged nourishment. Practiced for over 2,000 years, it is one of the most complete postpartum care systems in the world.</p>
    <p class="lede reveal">It is not a fad, not a restrictive ritual, and not reserved for Chinese families. What you eat in the first 30 days after birth affects your hormones, your milk supply, your energy, and your long-term recovery — for months to come.</p>
    <a href={route("/sample", locale) + "#gift"} class="hero-gift reveal">Buying this as a gift for someone? Start here →</a>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- REAL OUTCOMES -->
<section class="band band-paper">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">What mothers experience</p>
      <h2>Real outcomes from<br>{formatNumber(site.mothersServed)}+ families.</h2>
      <p>Mothers who follow the Zuo Yue Zi framework consistently report the same results — stronger milk supply, faster return of energy, reduced joint pain. These are not promises. They are what happens when the body gets what it actually needs.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="outcomes">
      <div class="outcome reveal">
        <div class="outcome-mark">i.</div>
        <h3>Stronger milk supply</h3>
        <p>Iron- and collagen-rich foods support lactation from Week 1.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="outcome reveal">
        <div class="outcome-mark">ii.</div>
        <h3>Faster energy return</h3>
        <p>Blood restoration in the first week makes the difference.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="outcome reveal">
        <div class="outcome-mark">iii.</div>
        <h3>Less joint pain</h3>
        <p>Warmth and circulation protect against postpartum wind.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="feature-quote reveal">
      <p class="q">"My milk came in so much that I ended up donating and feeding four babies. Any American non-Chinese mamas reading this: don't hesitate. This is the stuff that really nourishes you."</p>
      <p class="by">Michelle W. · Las Vegas</p>
      <p class="ctx">First-time mom, frozen delivery</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- THE WINDOW -->
<section class="band band-cream">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="window-grid">
      <div class="window-body reveal">
        <p class="eyebrow">The window</p>
        <h2>Why the first<br>30 days change<br>everything.</h2>
        <p>Your body just went through one of the most physically demanding events of your life. Childbirth involves profound blood loss and a massive expenditure of vital energy. Traditional Chinese medicine describes the postpartum body as in a state of deficiency, stasis, and cold — more open and more vulnerable than it has ever been.</p>
        <p>But vulnerability is also opportunity. That same openness makes this window uniquely powerful for healing. With the right nourishment and the right sequence, a woman can not only recover fully — she can emerge with a stronger constitution than she had before pregnancy.</p>
        <p class="window-quote">"In Chinese tradition, the first month after birth is not a burden to endure — it is the most important gift a woman can give herself."</p>
      </div>
      <div class="window-img reveal" role="img" aria-label="Warm bowl of traditional postpartum soup">
        <Svg36 />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- THREE PILLARS -->
<section class="band band-paper">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">The canonical structure</p>
      <h2>Zuo Yue Zi rests on<br>three pillars.</h2>
      <p>Across two millennia, Chinese postpartum care has been organized around three things, in this order. Food first. Herbs alongside. Rest underneath it all.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="three-pillars">
      <div class="pillar reveal">
        <div class="pillar-mark">i.</div>
        <h3>Food</h3>
        <p>Warm, iron- and collagen-rich, staged across 30 days. The foundation of every other pillar.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar reveal">
        <div class="pillar-mark">ii.</div>
        <h3>Herbs</h3>
        <p>Traditional postpartum formulas that work with the food to support blood, milk, and energy.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar reveal">
        <div class="pillar-mark">iii.</div>
        <h3>Rest</h3>
        <p>Sleep and gentle movement — described in classical teaching as "the world's greatest nourishment."</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FOUR PRINCIPLES -->
<section class="band band-cream">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">Four principles</p>
      <h2>What Zuo Yue Zi<br>actually protects.</h2>
      <p>Chinese postpartum care organizes recovery around four guiding principles. Each has a 2,000-year track record — and a straightforward modern explanation.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="principles">
      <div class="principle reveal">
        <p class="principle-tag">First</p>
        <p class="principle-tcm">避風寒 · Protect warmth</p>
        <h3>Guard against cold.</h3>
        <p>After birth, the body's defenses are lowered. Cold water, cold food, and drafts can penetrate deeply — causing joint pain and hormonal disruption that may not surface until years later. Warmth is protective, not superstitious.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="principle reveal">
        <p class="principle-tag">Second</p>
        <p class="principle-tcm">先清後補 · Sequence matters</p>
        <h3>Clear first, then nourish.</h3>
        <p>Rich food too soon is a burden, not a benefit. The stomach must first recover its ability to receive. Only after lochia clears and digestion stabilizes can the body convert nourishment into Qi, blood, and milk.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="principle reveal">
        <p class="principle-tag">Third</p>
        <p class="principle-tcm">動靜有度 · Rest with circulation</p>
        <h3>Move gently — rest, don't freeze.</h3>
        <p>Complete bed rest is a myth. Prolonged stillness impairs blood circulation and slows lochia discharge. Gentle movement within the first day supports uterine recovery. The goal is rest — not immobility.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="principle reveal">
        <p class="principle-tag">Fourth</p>
        <p class="principle-tcm">心平氣和 · Peace feeds recovery</p>
        <h3>Calm emotions, protect milk.</h3>
        <p>After birth, emotional swings are normal — not weakness. Stress directly restricts milk flow and can trigger mastitis. Sleep is the body's deepest medicine. Family support is not optional — it is part of the prescription.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- TAIWANESE TRADITION + 3 STAGES -->
<section class="band band-paper">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">Taiwanese tradition</p>
      <h2>The three-stage<br>recovery framework.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="stages-intro reveal">
      <p>Zuo Yue Zi exists across the Chinese-speaking world — but Taiwan is where the tradition never broke. The knowledge was most carefully preserved here, passed down through generations of mothers, refined by practitioners, and elevated into both a cultural expectation and a genuine craft. Taiwanese postpartum cooking is not a regional variation of the tradition. For many, it is the tradition at its most complete.</p>
      <p>Each stage is anchored by a signature dish Taiwanese families have prepared for generations. These are not comfort food — they are precision nutrition, chosen because they deliver exactly what the body needs at exactly the right moment.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="stages">

      <div class="stage-card reveal">
        <div class="stage-side">
          <p class="stage-week">Week 1</p>
          <p class="stage-phase">Mild</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stage-body">
          <h3>Pork liver soup</h3>
          <p class="stage-zh">豬肝湯 · replenish lost blood</p>
          <span class="stage-purpose">Iron restoration</span>
          <p>Childbirth depletes blood rapidly, and restoring it is the single most urgent priority in the first week. In Taiwanese tradition, pork liver soup is the first dish prepared for a new mother — often within days of birth. The reason is simple: you cannot rebuild on an empty foundation. Blood first. Everything else follows.</p>
          <div class="reasoning">
            <p class="reason-label">Why now and not later</p>
            <p class="reason-text">The body is still clearing lochia and digestion is fragile. This soup is gentle enough to receive, nourishing enough to matter. Rich, heavy food at this stage would overwhelm a system that is still clearing — not yet ready to build.</p>
            <a href={route("/guide/chinese-food-therapy", locale) + "#from-ingredients"} class="p7-link">What's in this dish — Chinese Food Therapy →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="stage-card reveal">
        <div class="stage-side">
          <p class="stage-week">Week 2</p>
          <p class="stage-phase">Warm</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stage-body">
          <h3>Eucommia kidney soup</h3>
          <p class="stage-zh">杜仲腰花 · strengthen the kidney and spine</p>
          <span class="stage-purpose">Kidney &amp; spine support</span>
          <p>Once blood is stabilized, the tradition turns its attention to the lower back and kidneys — the part of the body that bore nine months of pregnancy and labor. Many women who skip this stage develop chronic back pain that persists for years. This dish exists precisely to prevent that.</p>
          <div class="reasoning">
            <p class="reason-label">Why now and not earlier</p>
            <p class="reason-text">Restore blood first, strengthen the spine second. Attempting this before Week 1 is complete would be like reinforcing the walls before the foundation is set. By Week 2, the body is ready — and this is exactly when the support matters most.</p>
